{"title_page": "Bobby Roberts (footballer)", "text_new": "{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2014}}\n{{Use British English|date=July 2014}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name     = Bobby Roberts\n| image          = \n| caption        = \n| fullname       = Robert Roberts<ref>{{Hugman|16844|accessdate=30 April 2017}}</ref>\n| birth_date    = {{birth date and age|df=y|1940|9|2}}\n| birth_place = Scotland (shrek swamp)\n| height         = \n| position       = [[Midfielder]]\n| youthyears1    = \n| youthyears2    = \n| youthclubs1    = \n| youthclubs2    = \n| years1         = 1959\u20131963\n| years2         = 1963\u20131970\n| years3         = 1970\u20131972\n| years4         = 1972\u20131973\n| clubs1         = [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]]\n| clubs2         = [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]]\n| clubs3         = [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]]\n| clubs4         = [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]]\n| caps1          = 91\n| caps2          = 230\n| caps3          = 80\n| caps4          = 2\n| goals1         = 26\n| goals2         = 25\n| goals3         = 4\n| goals4         = 0\n| totalcaps      = 403\n| totalgoals     = 55\n| nationalyears1 = 1963\n| nationalteam1  = [[Scottish League XI]]<ref>http://www.londonhearts.com/SFL/players/bobbyroberts.html</ref>\n| nationalcaps1  = 1\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| medaltemplates = \n| club-update       = 11:17, 8 July 2009 (UTC)\n| ntupdate       = \n| manageryears1  = 1972\u20131973\n| manageryears2  = 1975\u20131982 \n| manageryears3  = 1982\u20131985\n| manageryears4  = 1987\u20131988\n| managerclubs1  = [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]] (Player-Coach)\n| managerclubs2  = [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]]\n| managerclubs3  = [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]]\n| managerclubs4  = [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]]\n}}\n'''Robert Roberts''' (born 2 September 1940) is a Scottish former [[association football|football]] player and manager, who played as a [[Midfielder]].<ref name=fl>{{cite web|title=Bobby Roberts|url=http://www.neilbrown.newcastlefans.com/player4/bobbyroberts.html|work=Post War English & Scottish Football League A - Z Player's Transfer Database|publisher=Neil Brown|accessdate=20 October 2011}}</ref>\n\n==Career==\nHe joined [[Motherwell F.C.|Motherwell]] from the Edinburgh Norton junior club, and went on to make almost 100 league appearances for them. He was made player of the year by the supporter's association for 1962.<ref>http://www.motherwell-mad.co.uk/news/loadfeat.asp?cid=ED22&id=450142</ref> Bobby moved to play in the [[Football League]] with [[Leicester City F.C.|Leicester City]] for the [[1963\u201364 in English football|1963-64 season]]. He went on to play 230 league matches for the club, and also appeared for Leicester in the [[1969 FA Cup Final]] and the second leg of the [[1965 Football League Cup Final]]. He subsequently transferred to [[Mansfield Town F.C.|Mansfield Town]].\n\nHe moved into coaching with a brief stint as player-coach with [[Coventry City F.C.|Coventry City]], and then in June 1975 he was appointed as manager of [[Colchester United F.C.|Colchester United]]. He remained at the club for seven years, and led them to promotion to the [[Football League Third Division]] in the [[1976\u201377 in English football|1976-77 season]].\n\nHe also managed [[Wrexham A.F.C.|Wrexham]] from 1982 to 1985 and [[Grimsby Town F.C.|Grimsby Town]] from 1987 to 1988, relinquishing the role to [[Alan Buckley]].\n\nSince then, Roberts has moved into scouting, working for [[Derby County F.C.|Derby County]],<ref>http://www.redpassion.co.uk/oldsite/issue15/horne.htm</ref> [[Tottenham Hotspur F.C.|Tottenham Hotspur]], [[Newcastle United F.C.|Newcastle United]] and [[Oxford City F.C.|Oxford City]].<ref>http://news.bbc.co.uk/sport1/hi/football/teams/o/oxford_utd/5115574.stm</ref>\n\n==Managerial statistics==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Team\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Nat\n!rowspan=\"2\"|From\n!rowspan=\"2\"|To\n!colspan=\"5\"|