03|publisher=[[Channel 4]]|archive-date=23 October 2007|accessdate=2018-04-08|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=3 | Day&nbsp;3\n| '''Entries/Twists''' || Jack, Jackiey, and Jade entered the house.\n|-\n| '''Tasks''' || The housemates were told to pack a small suitcase each that must last them three days and three nights.<ref name=\"get packing\">{{cite url|url=http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1075|title=Get Packing|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071023015716/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1075|date=2007-01-03|publisher=[[Channel 4]]|archive-date=23 October 2007|accessdate=2018-04-08|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> Big Brother announced that eight of the current housemates were to move to the House Next Door while the remaining three housemates were to stay in the main house. Danielle, Jo, Leo, Carole, Donny, Ian, Cleo and Dirk moved into the house next door and will become servants to the masters in the main house: Jermaine, Shilpa and Ken<ref name=\"servant quarters\">{{cite url|url=http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1078|title=Servants' Quarters|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20071022232129/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1078&articleMask=1|date=2007-01-05|publisher=[[Channel 4]]|archive-date=22 October 2007|accessdate=2018-04-08|url-status=live|df=dmy-all}}</ref> who were joined by Jade, her boyfriend Jack and her mother Jackiey.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071023015616/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1077&articleMask=1 Jade's Back]\", ''Channel 4's Official Big Brother site''. Retrieved 5 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n| '''Exits''' || Donny left the house voluntarily by climbing over the garden wall in the House Next Door after learning he would be a servant to Jade and her new extended family in the main House.<ref>\"[http://bigbrother.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds10796.html Donny ejected from house after wall jump] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070108103435/http://bigbrother.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds10796.html |date=8 January 2007 }}\", ''Digital Spy''. Retrieved 6 January 2007</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Day&nbsp;5\n| '''Exits''' || Ken Russell voluntarily left the House after arguing with the Goody family.<ref name=\"Ken leaves\">\"[http://bigbrother.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds10926.html Ken is next to quit] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070109082806/http://bigbrother.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds10926.html |date=9 January 2007 }}\", ''Digital Spy''. Retrieved 7 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n| '''General''' || Jade's grandparents entered the House as guests for dinner.  They left after the meal.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071022232139/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1110&articleMask=1 Guess Who's Coming To Dinner?]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 7 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;6\n| '''Tasks''' || The housemates were informed that they had passed the Masters and Servants task.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071023015626/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1124&articleMask=1 Task Masters]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 8 January 2007.</ref> Jo failed because she allowed Ken to make his own food at one point and Leo failed because he fell asleep during his shift.\n|-\n!| '''Day&nbsp;8'''\n| '''Exits''' || Jackiey was evicted from the Big Brother House. Jackiey was called to the Diary Room and informed she would leave the House via the Diary Room and would not say goodbye to her fellow housemates; the housemates observed Jackiey's eviction on the [[plasma screen]] in the kitchen.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071022232144/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1165&articleMask=1 Jackiey Gets The Heave Ho]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 10 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Day&nbsp;9\n| '''Nomination''' || The first round of nominations took place with Dirk and Leo up for eviction, they were joined by Carole as punishment for discussing nominations.<ref>\"[http://bigbrother.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds11250.html Carole, Dirk and Leo nominated!] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070113102018/http://bigbrother.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds11250.html |date=13 January 2007 }}\", ''Digital Spy''. Retrieved 11 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n| '''Punishments''' || Carole faced the vote automatically after it was revealed that Cleo and she had discussed nominations, the housemates were instructed to choose one of the pair to face the public vote.\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;10\n| '''Exits''' || Leo Sayer voluntarily left the House. He left the House by smashing the glass tube on the garden [[fire door]] barging through the camera run and through another door.  He proceeded to argue with security officers and programme producers before finally being granted his wish not to return. Carole was evicted with 77% of the votes<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://channel4.com:80/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1200&articleMask=1&housemateId Carole \u2013 You Have Been Evicted!]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 12 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;11\n| '''Tasks''' || Jermaine and Ian were tasked to take each other on in a Battle of the Tribute Bands: Steps vs The Jackson 5. They were chosen to be band leaders. Ian chose Jo, Jade and Jack while Jermaine chose Shilpa, Cleo, Dirk and Danielle to be their band members. They must sing and dance to the songs selected by Big Brother, Steps performed [[Deeper Shade of Blue]] and The Jackson 5 performed [[I Want You Back]]. The winner was decided by an online poll on the Big Brother website. The Jackson 5 won by 75% of the votes and were awarded platinum discs. All housemates were rewarded a Jackson 5 themed party.\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;13\n| '''Tasks''' || Housemates were required to complete an [[assault course]] in under nine minutes. The housemates failed this task<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://channel4.com:80/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1244 Slip Up]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 20 January 2007.</ref> and received a basic shopping budget.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071023015636/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1247 Unhappy Shoppers]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 20 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;14\n| '''General''' || Shilpa and Jade were involved in an argument with each other which began with a disagreement over an [[Oxo (food)|Oxo]] cube.  The argument increased the growing controversy surrounding the racist bullying of Shilpa.<ref name=\"BBC quote summary\">\"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/6282883.stm Big Brother controversy in quotes]\", BBC News. Retrieved 20 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Day&nbsp;15\n| '''Tasks''' || Housemates were set a task to divide into groups and create [[abstract art]] to express their emotions.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://channel4.com:80/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1279 But Is It Art?]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 20 January 2007.</ref> They passed the task and received champagne as a reward.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071023015646/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1282 The Unveiling]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 20 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n| '''Nominations''' || The second round of nominations took place.  Shilpa and Jade received the most nomination votes and were up for eviction. However, owing possibly to the controversy at the time, the results were not revealed until the Day 17: the day of the eviction.\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Day&nbsp;17\n| '''Tasks''' || Housemates were instructed to use their voices to perform [[William Tell Overture]],<ref>\"[http://www.channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1306 Housemates Blow Their Own Trumpets]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 21 January 2007.</ref> which they passed.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071023015652/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1306 Top Trumpets]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 21 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n| '''Exits''' || Jade became the third person to be evicted from the house with 82% of the votes.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071023015701/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1310 Jade, You Have Been Evicted]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 20 January 2007.</ref> Due to the controversy at the time, her eviction was not attended by a live audience.<ref name=\"no audience\">\"[http://news.bbc.co.uk/1/hi/entertainment/6277875.stm Crowd ban on Big Brother eviction]\", BBC News. Retrieved 20 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;19\n| '''Tasks''' || Housemates were given a task where they were required to make Big Brother [[laughter|laugh]].<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://channel4.com:80/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1329 Chuckle Brother]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 21 January 2007.</ref> They passed the task and received party food as a reward.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/*/http://channel4.com:80/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1340 Make 'Em Laugh]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 21 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;20\n| '''Tasks''' || The task was to perform a [[showgirl]] dance routine.<ref>\"[http://bigbrother.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds11899.html Housemates become showgirls for shopping] {{webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20070124110845/http://bigbrother.digitalspy.co.uk/article/ds11899.html |date=24 January 2007 }}\", ''Digital Spy''. Retrieved 22 January 2007.</ref> Housemates passed the task and received a luxury shopping budget.<ref>\"[https://web.archive.org/web/20071022232209/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1355 Can You Kick It?]\", ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 22 January 2007.</ref>\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Day&nbsp;21\n| '''Tasks''' || The housemates had to choose something they wanted under \u00a310. They had to answer questions about their fellow housemates. Each housemate had to choose another housemate and answer questions about the housemate. If a housemate got 3 out of 5 questions right, the housemate that the other housemate chose would have won their prize they selected before the task.\n|-\n| '''Nominations''' || The third and final round of nominations took place with Cleo, Dirk, Ian, Jo and Shilpa being nominated for the public vote.\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;22\n| '''Tasks''' || The housemates were each given a large ice cube with a token inside. Using only their mouth and tongue, they had to melt the ice cube enough for them to be able to retrieve the token with their hands. If all 8 housemates retrieved their token within 90 minutes, they would win an apr\u00e8s-ski party. Housemates passed the task.\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;24\n| '''Exits''' || Jo and Cleo were evicted together in a double eviction.\n|-\n! rowspan=2 | Day&nbsp;25\n| '''General''' || The housemates were asked questions submitted by the public.<ref name=\"Questions,Questions\"/>\n|-\n| '''Tasks''' || The housemates were instructed to devise four performances each based around a different genre: romantic comedy, film noir, action blockbuster and Bollywood musical. All past and present housemates must be portrayed by the final six housemates.<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20071023015721/http://channel4.com/entertainment/tv/microsites/B/bb7_celebrity/news/newsstory.jsp?id=1429&articleMask=1&housemateId= Made for TV] ''Channel Four's Official Big Brother Website''. Retrieved 26 January 2007.</ref> The housemates passed the task and therefore earned a three course sit down meal.\n|-\n!| Day&nbsp;26\n| '''Exits''' || Jack and Danielle left the house first on the final night together finishing in 6th and 5th place. Ian finished in 4th place and was followed later by Dirk who finished in 3rd place. Jermaine finished as runner-up with Shilpa leaving the house last as the winner of Celebrity Big Brother 2007.\n|}\n\n== Nominations table ==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align:center; width:100%; font-size:9pt; line-height:15px;\"\n|-\n! style=\"width:14%\"|\n! style=\"width:14%\"|Day 3\n! style=\"width:14%\"|Day 9\n! style=\"width:14%\"|Day 15\n! style=\"width:14%\"|Day 21\n! style=\"width:14%\" colspan=\"2\"|Day 26<br>Final\n! style=\"width:1%\"|Nominations<br>received\n|-\n! style=\"background:#000\" colspan=\"8\"|\n|-\n! Shilpa\n| style=\"background:#ccc\"|''Master<br>in Task'' || Jack,<br>Leo || Jade,<br>Jack || Dirk,<br>Jack || style=\"background:#73FB76\" colspan=\"2\"|'''Winner'''<br>(Day 26) || style=\"background:#73FB76\"|9\n|-\n! Jermaine\n| style=\"background:#ccc\"|''Master<br>in Task'' || Jo,<br>Danielle || Jade,<br>Jo || Danielle,<br>Jo || style=\"background:#D1E8EF\" colspan=\"2\"|'''Runner-up'''<br>(Day 26) || style=\"background:#D1E8EF\"|2\n|-\n! Dirk\n| style=\"background:#FBF373\"|''Servant<br>in Task'' || Ian,<br>Jermaine || Jade,<br>Jermaine || Jo,<br>Cleo || style=\"background:#ffffd