-7006-1012-9|ref=harv|url=https://archive.org/details/presidencyoffran00mcji}}; [https://archive.org/details/presidencyoffran00mcji online free]\n* {{cite book |ref= harv |last= Sainsbury |first= Keith |title= Churchill and Roosevelt at War: The War They Fought and the Peace They Hoped to Make |publisher= New York University Press |year= 1994 |isbn= 0-8147-7991-3 |url= https://archive.org/details/churchillrooseve0000sain }}\n* {{cite book |last=Smith |first=Jean Edward|authorlink=Jean Edward Smith|publisher=Random House | location =New York|title=FDR |url=https://archive.org/details/fdr00smit |url-access=registration |year=2007 |ref= harv}} 858pp\n{{refend}}\n\n==Further reading==\n{{Main|Bibliography of Franklin D. Roosevelt}}\n\n===Biographical===\n{{Refbegin|2}}\n* {{Citation | last = Black | first = Conrad | author-link = Conrad Black| year = 2005 | origyear = 2003 | title = Franklin Delano Roosevelt: Champion of Freedom |url=https://books.google.com/books?id=lYVCi70HaigC | isbn = 9781586482824 }}  1276pp interpretive detailed biography; [https://archive.org/details/franklindelanoro00blac online free]\n* Freidel, Frank. (1956) ''Franklin D. Roosevelt The Triumph'' (Little, Brown, 1956) vol 3 of 4-vol detailed scholarly biography covers 1929\u201332 [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.156788 online]\n* Freidel, Frank. (1956) ''Franklin D. Roosevelt: Launching the New Deal'' (1973) vol 4 of 4-vol detailed scholarly biography covers Nov. 1932 to July 1933. [http://www.tandfonline.com/doi/abs/10.1080/03612759.1974.9947207 online review]; [https://archive.org/details/franklindrooseve04fran online free]\n* Freidel, Frank. (1991)  ''Franklin D. Roosevelt: A Rendezvous with Destiny'', complete biography to 1945. 710pp [https://books.google.com/books?id=fRN2zUV5zNEC&printsec=frontcover#v=onepage&q&f=false excerpt]; also [https://archive.org/details/franklindroosevefre00frei online free]\n* {{cite book|author=Goodwin, Doris Kearns |title=No Ordinary Time: Franklin & Eleanor Roosevelt: The Home Front in World War II|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=Hfv-AwAAQBAJ&pg=PA7|year=1994|publisher=Simon and Schuster|isbn=9781476750576}}\n* Hamby, Alonzo. ''For the survival of democracy: Franklin Roosevelt and the world crisis of the 1930s'' (2004) [https://archive.org/details/forsurvivalofdem00hamb online free]\n* {{Citation | last = Pederson | first = William D | year = 2011 | title = A Companion to Franklin D. Roosevelt | publisher = Blackwell | series = Companions to American History}}; 35 essays by scholars emphasizing historiography. [https://www.questia.com/read/123510939/a-companion-to-franklin-d-roosevelt online]; [https://books.google.com/books?id=r4-UnSYARiMC&pg=PT23&dq=%22Chapter+One+FDR+Biographies%22&hl=en&sa=X&ved=0ahUKEwjtp6zZ-_bSAhVY5mMKHewpD1QQ6AEIHDAA#v=onepage&q=%22Chapter%20One%20FDR%20Biographies%22&f=false excerpt at Google]\n{{Refend}}\n\n===Scholarly topical studies===\n{{Refbegin|2}}\n* Badger, Anthony. ''The New Deal: The Depression Years, 1933\u20131940'' (2002).\n* Biles, Roger. ''A New Deal for the American People'' (Northern Illinois UP, 1991). \n* Brinkley, Douglas G. ''Rightful Heritage: Franklin D. Roosevelt and the Land of America'' (2016) [https://www.amazon.com/gp/product/0062089234/  excerpt]; On FDR's environmental and conservation beliefs & policies.\n* Clarke, Jeanne Nienaber. ''Roosevelt's Warrior: Harold L. Ickes and the New Deal'' (1996)\n* Gosnell, Harold. ''Champion Campaigner Franklin D Roosevelt'' (1952) [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.157588 online]\n* [[Alonzo Hamby|Hamby, Alonzo L.]] ed. ''The New Deal, Analysis & Interpretation'' (Longman Publishing Group, 1981). short excerpts from 14 scholars; [https://archive.org/details/TheNewDealAnalysisAndInterpretation online in TIF format]\n* Howard, Donald S. ''WPA and federal relief policy'' (1943), 880pp; highly detailed report by the independent Russell Sage Foundation.\n* {{Citation | last = Leuchtenburg | first = William E |authorlink=William Leuchtenburg | year = 2005 | title = Showdown on the Court | journal = Smithsonian | volume = 36 | number = 2 | pages = 106\u201313 | issn = 0037-7333 | type = fulltext }}; 1937 Supreme Court fight\n* Meriam; Lewis. ''Relief and Social Security'' The Brookings Institution. 1946. Highly detailed analysis and statistical summary of all New Deal relief programs; 900 pages [https://archive.org/details/in.ernet.dli.2015.275609 online]\n* Morris, Charles R. ''A Rabble of Dead Money: The Great Crash and the Global Depression: 1929\u20131939'' (PublicAffairs, 2017), 389 pp. [https://www.nytimes.com/2017/04/21/books/review/rabble-of-dead-money-charles-r-morris-great-depression-wall-street.html online review]\n* {{Citation | last = Pederson | first = William D | year = 2011 | title = A Companion to Franklin D. Roosevelt|publisher=Wiley-Blackwell |isbn=9781444330168 }}, 768 pages; essays by scholars covering major historiographical themes. [https://www.questia.com/read/123510939/a-companion-to-franklin-d-roosevelt online]\n* Purcell, Aaron D. ed ''The New Deal and the Great Depression'' (Kent State UP, 2014) 234pp  [https://muse.jhu.edu/article/617053/summary online review]\n* {{Citation | author-link = Arthur M. Schlesinger, Jr.| last = Schlesinger | first = Arthur M. Jr | year = 1957\u201360 | title = The Age of Roosevelt }}, the 3-volume classic narrative history. Strongly supports FDR.\n** Arthur M. Schlesinger, Jr. ''The Age of Roosevelt vol 1: The Crisis Of The Old Order (1919\u20131933)'' (1956) [https://archive.org/download/in.ernet.dli.2015.462866/2015.462866.The-Age.pdf online] to March 1933\n** Arthur M. Schlesinger, Jr. ''The Age Of Roosevelt vol 2: The Coming of the New Deal'' (1958) [https://archive.org/download/in.ernet.dli.2015.178732/2015.178732.The-Coming-Of-The-New-Deal-The-Age-Of-Roosevelt.pdf online] covers 1933\u201334\t\n** Arthur M. Schlesinger, Jr. ''The Age of Roosevelt vol 3: The Age of Upheaval'' (1960); [https://archive.